## Category 2: Embedded JSON API via Chromium (Fast)
These websites do not have a public JSON URL, but they inject a massive hidden JSON payload (Next.js data or LD+JSON) directly into the HTML code of their product pages. We will use Chromium to open their sitemap, visit the pages, and extract the hidden JSON data without having to parse complex HTML elements.
15. **Gymshark** (Extracts `__NEXT_DATA__` JSON from HTML)
16. **Skims** (Extracts `application/ld+json` structured data from HTML)

## Category 3: Pure HTML Scraping via Chromium (Slowest)
These websites are custom-built (like Salesforce Commerce Cloud), and their APIs are completely locked down or disabled entirely (returning 404 or 410 Gone errors when tested). For these, we have absolutely no choice but to use Chromium to open the browser, load the page, and manually extract titles, prices, and stock from the visual HTML elements.
